# Docs Rules

## Architecture — Where Files Live

The Docusaurus site lives in `docs/` but **doc content does not live inside `docs/`**.
Content is co-located with the package it describes:

| Section | Source files | Route prefix |
|---------|-------------|--------------|
| Ingest worker | `packages/ingest-worker/docs/*.md` | `/` (root) |
| Supabase | `supabase/docs/*.md` | `/supabase/` |

Do **not** put doc pages in `docs/docs/` — that directory doesn't exist and the site isn't configured to read from it.

## Adding a New Page

1. Add a `.md` file to the appropriate source directory (`packages/ingest-worker/docs/` or `supabase/docs/`).
2. Include frontmatter at the top:
   ```md
   ---
   title: My Page Title
   sidebar_label: Short Label
   ---
   ```
3. Sidebars are **autogenerated** from the filesystem — no manual sidebar entry is needed unless you want custom ordering or grouping.

## Adding a New Doc Section (New Plugin)

When a new package needs its own doc section:

1. Add the source `.md` files under `<package>/docs/*.md`.
2. Add a new plugin entry in `docs/docusaurus.config.ts`:
   ```typescript
   ['@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs', {
     id: 'my-section',
     path: '../packages/my-package/docs',
     routeBasePath: 'my-section',
     sidebarPath: './sidebarsMySection.ts',
   }]
   ```
3. Create the sidebar file `docs/sidebarsMySection.ts`:
   ```typescript
   import type {SidebarsConfig} from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';
   const sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {
     mySectionSidebar: [{type: 'autogenerated', dirName: '.'}],
   };
   export default sidebars;
   ```
4. Add a navbar item in `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` under `themeConfig.navbar.items`.

## Running Locally

The docs site uses **Node.js + npm**, not Bun. Use npm scripts from within `docs/`:

```bash
cd docs
npm install       # first time / after dependency changes
npm start         # dev server at http://localhost:3000
npm run build     # production build to docs/build/
npm run serve     # preview the production build
npm run clear     # clear Docusaurus cache (use when pages don't update)
```

Node.js ≥ 20 is required.

## Mermaid Diagrams

Mermaid is enabled via `@docusaurus/theme-mermaid`. Use fenced code blocks:

````md
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  A->>B: Hello
```
````

## Frontmatter Reference

| Key | Required | Purpose |
|-----|----------|---------|
| `title` | yes | Page `<title>` and default sidebar label |
| `sidebar_label` | no | Overrides the sidebar display name |
| `sidebar_position` | no | Numeric ordering within the sidebar group |

## Do Not

- Edit files inside `docs/node_modules/`
- Put content in `docs/src/pages/` unless it is a standalone custom React page (not a standard doc)
- Run `bun` commands in `docs/` — use `npm`
- Edit the generated `docs/build/` output directly
